2.10	Dmitri_Furmanov	Dmitry Furmanov	Dmitry Andreyevich Furmanov (Russian: ; 7 November 1891 â€“ March 15, 1926) was a Russian writer. During the Russian Civil War he joined the Red Army and served as a Bolshevik commissar. He is well-known for his novel Chapayev about Vasily Chapayev, a Red Army officer and a hero of the Civil War. The novel is available in English translation.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/Furmanow_painting_by_malyutin.jpg/220px-Furmanow_painting_by_malyutin.jpg
